<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91245/33: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-30T16:00:00+02:00">July 30,
                                    1943—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 30—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4969. Department’s 3621, June 10, 10 p.m. We approached Foreign Office
                            again on United Press teletype telegraphic requirements in India and
                            have just been told that a definite reply from the Government of India
                            was expected shortly. Meanwhile, Foreign Office promises to continue to
                            maintain pressure on Government of India.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>